message.content:
cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about multi-task learning in computer vision, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel sparse, non-parametric approach using regularization and convex optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of Reproducing Kernel Hilbert Spaces and the focus on recovering interpretable structures could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
